Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity, readability, and versatility. 
It is widely used for various applications, including web development, data science, artificial intelligence, automation, and more.

Key Features of Python:
Easy to Learn & Readable – Python uses simple and intuitive syntax, making it beginner-friendly.
Interpreted Language – Code is executed line by line, making debugging easier.
Dynamically Typed – No need to declare variable types explicitly.
Extensive Libraries & Frameworks – Python has powerful libraries like NumPy, Pandas, TensorFlow, Django, and Flask.
Cross-Platform – Python code runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
Open Source & Community Support – A vast community contributes to Python's development and resources.